This function checks if the internal data cache has been invalidated. If it needs updating, the code invalidates and refreshes the necessary frame before returning.

```python
def types(self):
        """The dictionary of column name/type pairs."""
        if not self._ex._cache.types_valid():
            self._ex._cache.flush()
            self._frame(fill_cache=True)
        return dict(self._ex._cache.types)
```

By using `fill_cache=True`, this method guarantees that even if the cache is missing or stale, the column types are refreshed from the source.
